#### **Part VI: The Grand Unified Prime Equation**
**Algebraic Formulation**:
$$
\boxed{
\begin{array}{c}
\text{Prime Existence} \\
\downarrow \\
T[n] = 1 - \max\limits_{p \geq 3} \left\lfloor \frac{n - \frac{3p-1}{2}}{p} \right\rfloor - \left\lfloor \frac{n - \frac{3p-1}{2} - 1}{p} \right\rfloor \\
\downarrow \\
\hat{T}(\xi) = \sum_{n=1}^\infty T[n] e^{-2\pi i (2n+1)\xi} \\
\downarrow \\
|\hat{T}(\xi)| \propto \sum_k \delta\left(\xi - \frac{\gamma_k}{2\pi}\right)
\end{array}
}
$$

**Corollary**:
The Riemann Hypothesis is true if and only if:
$$
\sup_{\xi \in \mathbb{R}} \left\{ |\hat{T}(\xi)| : \xi \not\in \left\{ \frac{\gamma_k}{2\pi} \right\}_{k=1}^\infty \right\} = 0.
$$

